  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Women-Owned Small Business (WOSB) set-aside obligations for FY2026 to date total $510M across 1,881 awards with an average award size of $271K. Obligations are down 59.8% year over year, and current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date). Historical comparisons show obligations of $857M in FY21, $936M in FY22, $1.2B in FY23, $1.3B in FY24, and $1.3B in FY25. The Department of Defense is the single largest buyer in FY2026 to date at $265M, followed by the Department of Homeland Security at $63.9M and the Department of Commerce at $40.1M. Top vendor receipts in FY2026 to date range from $18.5M for INTELLECT SOLUTIONS, LLC to $10.2M for RESEARCH MANAGEMENT CONSULTANTS INC. Leading industry categories by obligations are Other Computer Related Services at $99.6M and Engineering Services at $91M, with major shares also in research, medical, and consulting-related NAICS codes.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "What is the current size and trajectory of WOSB set-aside obligations?",
        "body": "Total obligations are $510M for FY2026 to date across 1,881 awards, with an average award size of $271K. Obligations are down 59.8% year over year. By comparison, obligations were $1.3B in FY25 and $1.3B in FY24. FY21 through FY23 obligations were $857M, $936M, and $1.2B respectively."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies, vendors, and industries account for the largest shares in FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "The Department of Defense accounts for $265M of obligations, followed by the Department of Homeland Security at $63.9M and the Department of Commerce at $40.1M. Top vendors include INTELLECT SOLUTIONS, LLC at $18.5M and DTECHLOGIC LLC at $17.4M. Leading industries are Other Computer Related Services at $99.6M and Engineering Services at $91M, with significant obligations also in research and medical services."
      }
    ]
  },
